What is an asynchronous call?

An Asynchronous Function is a function that delays part of it's functionality to be executed separately from the rest of the logic in the function.
Asynchronous functions uses callbacks to report their results back to invoker.

How does angular/javascript handle asynchronous calls?
Promises AND .THEN

A promise is:
If I give you a callback
You PROMISE to invoke it
When you have my answer 
[OPTIONAL]and pass my answer in as a parameter
